caption: Absolutely yummy!  Great spot to catch late night meals and drinks!!

This location close to the Hillsborough river is in a former industrial electrical building that has been converted. It has nice outdoor seating and interesting interior decor. The burger was exceptional and the Caesar Salad was good. Hannah our server was very nice.
Great food great staff! The rolled shrimp are delicious 😋
Amazing thank you for a great experience
Outstanding experience. Curtis was exceptional and every part of the meal was perfect. Couldn’t have been better!
Steak was about as great of quality as waffle house at 3am. No flavor tough and $52. Mac n cheese was good though🙄. Overall not impressed.
Food was delicious. That mac n cheese and fried chicken was everything!!
Really good service and food
We've been to Steelbach many times. Service is always great, and the food is amazing! We most recently had brunch, and it did not disappoint. So many fun options! Definitely a must try!
The atmosphere was fun and the food was absolutely amazing. I would highly recommend this place!
Tampa's well kept secret is out, of this place you will spout! A bit of bragging is due, tasty morsels is the clue! We liked it so well that within a week, we visited twice to fill our cheeks!

Drinks, dinner, and dessert were all delicious. Our waitress Stevie (I think that was her name) was absolutely fantastic and paired everything perfectly. We had the bone in filet, the brussel sprouts, sweet potato and for dessert carrot cake.  We highly recommend this place and will definitely be back again soon.
Great food and service....sat outside....quiet and great to relax
Great food and ambience!

Seated immediately at the bar (first come first serve) on a packed Saturday night - service was thoughtful and impeccable. Highly recommend the shitake mushroom infused signature cocktail "Shitake Happens". These two New Yorkers will be back next time!
Amazing service and food! Ambiance on point! Get the Flight mimosas and monkey bread!!!! No complaints! It was just what I needed for this mama with almost no days off!!!!!
There was nothing bad about this place. Great menu,  just couldn't get a table since I didn't make a reservation. This is the place to be on a Friday night.

Overall, this place is fine. Is it fantastic? Absolutely not. Average at best.  First, the GOOD: All staff were very friendly and knowledgeable on menu items. The atmosphere was upscale without being snooty. We appreciated the laidback feel.  The BAD: Please know there is just about zero distancing between tables here. They’re 100% capacity. If that makes you nervous, Steelbach is not the place for you.  The UGLY: My lord, the Buffalo cauliflower was absolutely one of the most disgusting things I’ve ever been served in a restaurant. I’m a fan of it when it’s done correctly, but Steelbach’s is horrendously over-smoked. It tasted like the burnt scraps from the grill. Gross.

Their Buffalo cauliflower appetizer is delicioso.  Their steak was cooked perfectly (med rare) but a tad bit pricy for “a la carte” steak Only 1-2 beers on draft, but they had 6 or so local beers in cans/bottles
Great food and great service. Staff made all necessary efforts to provide a comfortable and safe environment.

Tbh, this spot is perfect for when you have a hangover or just want to eat on the lighter side, not for an after the gym meal lol but I’ve been a couple of times and enjoyed the food and atmosphere 👍🏼

Car salesman one liner for a waiter who talked to some ladies in the waiting area more than he filled our water glasses. Food took an hour and the manager came over to apologize but the kicker was my $60 bone in 12 oz filet included a 6 oz bone. Not our night I guess.

We had Curtis as our waiter, who provide not only fast service, but quality service.  He had a Great attitude, on always was on top of making sure all his tables were taken care of.  The food was perfect and ended the night nicely.  Most prime spots in Tampa on Friday and Saturday night similar to Steelbach do not offer the same quality of service in my opinion. Thanks for setting the bar high

Over priced. Herb baked potatoes was very bland. The buffalo cauliflower was horrible.  Both our steaks we asked for medium rare. They came out very rare. Asked the server to cook longer and it still came back very rare. The mac and cheese was good. The Fried chicken was good. But we spent $200 for 4 people and only 2 plates were good. Definitely did not get our money worth.

Poor service, worse food. Cocktails were good though, so there’s that.  Would not recommend:  - Caesar salad (soggy) - Brussels sprouts (drenched in sauce) - Grouper (overcooked) - Lamb (overcooked and flavorless)
Best attention as always  , nothing but great people working there , they will find the way to serve you with what you need no matter what !!!!

Bery nice ambiance. The staff is great and the food is pretty good. I've gone twice. Two reasons for the 4 stars instead of 5. #1 the food isn't consistent. The first time I went with a friend and everything was amazing! The second time I took my mom and niece and the flavor/seasonings were off. The mac'n'cheese was good, but I could tell that someone different made it and that shouldn't be. Also, the broccoli had waaay too much sauce and was slightly overcooked and the collard greens were also not the same. #2 I ordered the chicken and it came out just barely warm which  is unacceptable. My friend wants to go back, I'm sceptical, but will return to try it out again. Pics are from 2 different visits
Enjoyable experience. Great food. Great service from our waitress Stevie.
Overpriced ultra modern menu.  Better options in town include Meat Market.  Clueless, obtuse staff.

Greeted by total slugs at the hostess station that made us feel like we were interrupting their conversation.  Seated, with reservations - waited  15 minutes for someone to take our drink order before giving up and moving to the bar.  Bartender was very engaging and responsive but food was brought from kitchen with little thought on timing. Our plates were never cleared in between courses. Overpriced and way below expectations.  Had a great brunch here several weeks ago. Never again for dinner.

Very good burgers !!! We has lunch on the patio and tables are nicely spaced out, service is fast and food is excellent. Hangover burgers were made with amazing quality beef, but what surprised even more that kids burgers were almost as big, and very tasty - unlike kids meals in most places. Great servIce and lively atmosphere.

The food is good, but you can probably find similar/better food in about 90% of Tampa. I wont be coming back here after I made a 12 pm reservation and had to wait 1 HR (even though there were several 4 people tables open) because the hostess said the "owner is coming". About 45 minutes into my wait time they proceed to sit a group without reservation and when I ask to speak to the manager the hostess says "we don't have a table for you" (I am unsure what the purpose of a reservation is then....) The manager then tells me that they didn't realize they sat another group and that i was waiting for an hour (poor internal communication). Needless to say the customer service here is subpar. Ill take my money elsewhere... oh and the owner came with about 10 people so he wasn't even going to sit at a four person table.
Don’t get a latte here.  Probably my fault but this was only place in Armature Works that serves coffee now that union closed.
I frequently come here for lunch. Food is great and staff friendly.
Incredible lunch and service along with a great location.
Great service. Fantastic steaks. Their mac and cheese an brussel sprout are very good.. Good carrot cake and organic dulce de leche cheesecake. Definite recommend.
Great steak!
The tomahawk steak is not as good as Flemings', but the cucumber cocktail makes it all worthwhile. Nice friendly staff.
Excellent food and a great locatio
The food is amazing. The menu is short and sweet. The wait staff is professional. One of the best experiences I've had dining out in Tampa

The bartenders are so great! We were waited on by the older gentlemen Patrick. He was really in depth with describing the drinks and making good suggestions. Really great experience thanks to him. We haven’t even tried the food yet but 5 stars!
GREAT FOOD GREAT SERVICE GREAT ATMOSPHERE
Great drinks and appetizers!!! And that's all we had.

We loved the food, the everything muffin and the Hangover burger was delicious,I took my egg off the burger put my it on the side with the  potatoes. The only critique would be the Smothered Corn Cakes, they were delicious but very skimpy on the pulled pork considering the description. Great servIce and wonderful atmosphere.
Had a great experience. Really enjoyed the creative appetizers, salads, and side dishes. They have great steaks as well.
Excellent brunch. Exotic preparation. Very good service.
Amazing Brunch! Great restaurant and atmosphere inside or outside. Love their deviled eggs appetizer. Fantastic biscuits, eggs, and fried green tomatoes. Put the honey hot sauce on them!
I overheard the wait staff complaining that they weren't tipped enough, despite receiving a tip above the auto gratuity for large parties.
Splendid Food,Great Selection of Food * Spirits & Wonderful  Ambience Ouside & inside..   2 Thumbs up!!!
Delicious food and wonderful atmosphere. Felt a little crowded as evening went on. Great service.

We love visiting the Armature works, and this was our first visit to Steelbach. We were very impressed with both the food and the service. We ate at the bar as we hadn't booked ahead of time, and Joseph the head barman was highly efficient, knowledgeable and friendly. The food was outstanding, and prices very reasonable indeed. We will definitely dine there in the very near future.

The grouper and rice was a delicious and refreshing meal, the flavor and texture of the rice was unexpectedly light and pleasant. The popovers were a veryyy tasty starter. Our waiter was just the right amount of friendly/attentive and he made helpful recommendations based on my food preferences.

A great place to sit and enjoy superb food with your friends!  Menu had some great variety and you’ll be sure to find something you like.  We started with the popovers, the pimento tartine and some cocktails, then had the burgers and NY strip steak. Sides of creamed greens and Brussel sprouts.  Service (Stevie) was attentive and chipper. Did not feel pressured to order eat and get out (“turn and burn”). We took our time and really enjoyed our time here.  (Sorry I didn’t think about posting until I was almost finished)
Love this place. Mac & cheese used to be better; but the service, atmosphere, drinks & food are AMAZING
Service was second to none, steak was delicious but I could live on that mac and cheese
Excellent. Not one downside to this restaurant.
Great steak totally worth the money waiter knew the drink menu off the top off his head forgot his name he was great tall skinny guy
Great drinks and atmosphere.

Pancakes with pulled pork and a spicy sauce, who knew that could be so yummy.  They lose a star because they don't space dinners enough. I stopped eating and left because they started seating so many people near me.
Great service!!!
Ordered NY strip steak. All too TOUGH not  tender at all...no flavor ....too expensive for what we got.  You have to pay for sides separately. If you wanted sides you had to pay like $10 fff for each
Good 👍🏾

We went to dinner tonight with 4 adults and 5 children. We were greeted by our waitress, Ivy. She was super sweet and knowledgeable of all items on the menu and had great suggestions for drinks (make sure to ask for her)! The adults shared 4 different appetizers (my fav was goat cheese app and shrimp eggrolls) and 4 different entrees - everything was absolutely delish! Steak was amazing to say the least. This was not our 1st time and most definitely will not be the last!
Such great atmosphere, food, and service. A great place for date night or a special celebration.
5 star service. 5 star high quality lunch. Each meal was tastefully and cleverly prepared. Pricing is fair, but you are actually getting more than what you pay for with quality and quantity.

We had an excellent New Years Eve dinner with Steelbach last night. Great food, excellent wine pairings with each course, and wonderful service on a very night! Pics are of the four course prefix meal and wine pairings.
The food was Amazing! We had the new year's menu but if the rest of the food is as good a what they gave this time we will definitely be back!
Good food, good drinks, and great service.
Great food, great service!

We came for brunch and got seated inside right away. We ordered the hangover burger and the bbq corn pancakes and both were scrumptious!! For the foodies like me it was a great surprise in Tampa. Great ambiance and a big bar inside. Absolutely recommend.
username: As for me and my House LLC

caption: Went here for brunch yesterday, was very good. Although we didn't have a reservation we were able to be seated right away at a bar top. The menu has excellent choices. I had the Sammie's steak sandwich, was very good, could have easily fed 2 but I didn't give up any 😁
Delicious, great service

Bossman had are Christmas party there.  ALL of the food was VERY very salty! Drinkers enjoyed it, sober people didn't even try to eat it. Most of us grabbed burger on our way home. Music was TOO loud. We had to shout at our neighbors! Pretty environment! Nice staff! We weren't impressed and will never waste OUR money to go back!
Great atmosphere and service. The food is excellent. This restaurant is located in Armature Works and is easy access from the street.  The steak and cream collard greens are really good.

I had been wanting to go here for the longest and I finally made it. I was able to make a reservation for brunch and was able to sit outside. Today was a beautiful Florida day to be outside and enjoy, and that is exactly what happened. First off the Flight of Mimosas really took me in. I had to walk it off and drink water for the rest of the afternoon as I was pretty buzzed. There was a blackberry, lemon/citrus, watermelon, and then my favorite strawberry rose!!! Our service was pretty amazing. Hats off to Joshua and his A one service. He was very friendly and even though they were out of the appetizers of our choice, he went and asked the chef if they could make a fresh batch for us and sure enough they did. The chef came out and hand delivered it to us and took a bow! We felt special! My first time having monkey bread, and happily took the rest home! This was my first time trying eggs Benedict let alone it being over a pork belly and biscuit but it was sooo flavorful. There was no need to add any salt and pepper. Then came what my special guest tried... a loaded up corn flour pancake with pulled pork, coleslaw, onions, topped with a lemon maple syrup and smoked butter... LOVED IT! So many flavors in your mouth it was explosive. Everything was so fresh!!! I truly recommend this spot if you haven’t went always. This is a hidden gem for sure.
Amazing
The food is AMAZING! The staff & atmosphere was very welcoming. We had a party of 18 and we never waited for anything!
Ambience - very good Food - excellent Noise - average Lighting - good Parking - ok. First come first come basis  Highly recommend for birthdays, anniversary or to celebrate any special occasions.
Awesome place ...recommend to visit.
Lovely outdoor space and delicious food

Great service, friendly atmosphere, awesome food! I had the steak frites and roasted vegetables. They were both tantalizing to my taste buds and satisfying to my tummy. The steak was cooked to perfection and the roasted vegetables were nestled on a sauce like I've never had. All I know was it was purple and tasted like a little bit of heaven. I couldn't eat it all and even when I heated it up later it was perfection. When I return to Temple I will definitely return to Steelbach.

Having to give good food a one star for potentially exposing my fiance and I to COVID.  We sat outside to minimize contact and were the only table seated outdoors. We kept our masks on anytime the server came to speak to us, however our server would continously PULL his mask down to speak to us, defeating the entire purpose of wearing a mask and of us sitting outdoors.  I did tell him to please not do that, and he no longer did, but it was extremely uncomfortable and we had to quarantine after to make sure we did not get sick.
Poutine and charcuterie were amazing

Having eaten here 3 times now, it is one of my favorite places to dine. The staff is attentive, professional and knowledgeable while the cuisine is top shelf. Last night, my friend and I had the rib eye and Tomahawk and it was one of the best steaks we've encountered. Peter, our server, was patient and wasn't afraid to have a laugh with us. Highly recommended place to eat.

Spent Sunday brunch there with my brother and friends. Didn't wait long for a booth. Joe, the waiter, was attentive and friendly. The burger was incredible. Bacon was thick...had a sweet taste...and potatoes were well cooked. When finished, you can take your drinks outside and walk through Armature Works or other outdoor venues nearby. As a side note, if you're a single bachelor like myself, the 'scenery' is nice too. Will definitely be back!
The lamb was devine!
Great as usual
Best restaurant in Tampa, the BEST!  Not kidding

Food was gross. All of the meats we had were dry and the biscuits couldn’t be saved with water or any beverage.  Service was beyond trash. I wouldn’t spend my money here if Jesus himself asked me to voyage here. There is no way our server wanted to help us, he came back every 30 mins to check on us which resulted in a simple lunch transforming into a 3 hour situation.  I cannot express the lack of customer service that was experienced during my visit.  Disappointed is an understatement  Food was severely under par for a table visit total of 600.00  Tip was included but Kenneth  did not deserve even 5.00  Quite literally some of the worst service I have every experienced in my life.  He ruined my friends birthday and she even set a reservation for this place weeks in advance.  Honestly NEVER Visiting this PLACE AGAIN..

We dined here on Friday evening with a group of 8. We had reservations at 8:30, arrived a few minutes early, and were seated right away. Kyle was our server and he did an incredible job of taking care of our group.  The food was fabulous. Definitely order the popovers...absolutely delicious.  The grouper was recommended by Kyle, and it was delightful. Others in our group had the spit chicken, fried chicken, pork chop, and steak. Brussels sprouts and truffle Mac and cheese are also amazing. Overall excellent food, wine, and service!
Service is always excellent even when they have a full house. The service here is outstanding. It has a nice atmosphere.
Excelente food and service.

I like the service and the food. I went for brunch and verything was delicious. The place is well located. The outside area is beautiful for a morning breakfast while the inside is great for later in the day.
Great food, great service, beautiful location. A new favorite spot!

Steelbach is a fine dining experience. The food has a inspired twist that sets it apart from other dinning experiences. The dishes my wife and I had were excellent. I will be back to try there steaks and a few other things on the menu. But I will be getting that Baked Potato and Avocado and Fennel saled again!
Excellent food. Loved the hangover burger for lunch. The food is well worth the price and I will certainly go back. Sit outside it is much more comfortable and the view is very nice.
This place was awesome, the food, the interior, the location and the delicious cocktails can't wait to come back during our next visit to Tampa.
Delicious food and outstanding service! Our waiter was amazing! The fried chicken was to die for and my husband loved his lamb! We'll definitely be going back!

Me and my wife came for a brunch on Sunday, and we have been waiting for our food over 46 minutes. And food  was not good at all. Breakfast potatoes was blend as well as fried chicken. Steak sandwich was hard to eat because meat was really tough. Overall not a good experience.

HORRIBLE experience! I am so disappointed because first time I was here 1 year ago and everything was so good, but this time it was awful.  1. Half of the kitchen stuff didn’t wear a mask! It made me feel so unsafe and frustrated because of their irresponsibility!  2. We have been waiting 40-45 minutes for two sandwiches. Are you serious?  3. My fried chicken and potatoes did not have any flavour. It was so blend. My husband’s steak was so chewy.  I don’t know what has to happen to make me to come back to this restaurant. I think, you have to change management in your kitchen to become more organised and to give food in time.

After many recommendations we made reservations for dinner....that was our first mistake, we arrived 5 min early and had to wait approx 20min, was told a large party just sat and the kitchen was getting slammed Once seated Samantha finally arrived so we went ahead and ordered drinks and food at the same time Our drinks arrived about 15 min later, was told the bar was busy....our steaks and sides arrived..but not our salad...so they then brought it while all food was on table.  Cut into our steaks, cold in center...extremely rare .both the tables next to us had already sent their steak back..and we really didn't want to but had no choice.  The picture shows how my steak came back...burnt to a crisp on the outside..the manager placed our steaks down and walked away, not a single word.   Our bill was $151 !!!!  This place is poorly managed,  grill chef needs to be replaced and customer service needs to be made a priority.  We dine out frequently and travel often..this has been one of our worse experiences..waitress told us its a new kitchen and she can cook better🤔😯

Food was great I order a the fried chicken meal. They gave me a an entire chicken without warning. I could have split it with my girl. The server should have warned us of how much food we were ordering... not everyone wants leftovers

From the area and this was the second time coming to this restaurant.  My boss and his wife were in town and I wanted a nice place to go to dinner on a Thursday night.  Waiter was far from energetic and substandard compared to first experience.  Food was okay, but not worth the price point of $100+ per guest.  I highly recommend you place a filter on your ice machines.  My mixed drink smelled like fishy Tampa water and killed the drink flavor.  I said something to the waiter and he simply said "sorry about that."  Guess its normal.  Fortunately, everyone else in my party drank wine.  If you go, I recommend you either get wine or get a drink without ice.  Wife and I both agree we won't be back.  Not worth the price point...especially if your looking for something a little more upscale.  Unfortunate...because the location and atmosphere are great.

Personally I disdain a reduced brunch fare but that is my personal choice. Regardless the waiter wanted to be anywhere but serving our table. Messed up drink orders, didn't bring appetizers, missed up beer selection. Didn't bring salt and pepper when asked. Rude. Portions were small. Biscuits hard and overcooked. Yet super proud of their pricing. I love paying for a good meal, great atmosphere and good service. Here I spent $50 on a great atmosphere and staff who thought I wasn't good enough to dine with them.
great brunch -- get the monkey bread to share!! cute spot in a great location
Great steak house.   Went during covid early in the day.   Very nice cuts, and prepared as requested.
Steelbach is an upscale restaurant with great food and drinks. I love the Short Rib Mezze and Sausage board - pictured here.
The food was perfect! Our server Kyle , just amazing! Best meal and service ever!!!

I really enjoyed the ambiance and overall experience. The employees are dressed down, but it seems like a more upscale place. Fancy spins on southern food, but good overall. It's definitely the kind of place where you can share, especially the sides or get something so you can take it home. I had the grouper and mac'n cheese. The mac was piping hot and the fish not so much. Still tasty. I'd go back and try other items like their fried chicken and creamed collard greens. (I'm not the end all be all for opinions on fried chicken and collard greens, BUT not going to lie I'm nervous.) Maybe I won't be disappointed.
Everything was delicious! Service was great as usual!
i like it here, excellent food & service. the place has a nice feel to it. food and atmosphere reminds me of atlanta.
The food was super appetizing. Looking forward to coming back with my coworkers. The bill won't break you.
the food was super appetizing. service treated us so nice. this place has a great atmosphere.
Great flavors, nicely cooked food and good drinks. Our waitress was sweet.

It's a very lovely place, the service was impeccable from the hostess, our server and the manager.  I love duck and was excited to order it! It arrived with a underdone gummy skin, completely inedible, so my server graciously took it back to have the skin cooked longer.  It came book looking much better however, they cook the meat on a wood burning grill which made the taste completely overwhelmed the flavor.  The manager came over and apologized and asked if I would like something else.  I ordered the rack of lamb, and had 4 tiny ribs, and also completely charred by the grill and took a bite and all I tasted was char. I took 2 bites and left it on the table.  Everything is ala carte, and the side broccoli was also charred from the grill.  Paid 200.00 with tip and left hungry.  My suggestion to the proprietor, you have beautiful cuts of meat, you should give people an option if they want it cooked with our without wood.  I would have loved to taste the flavor of the meats.
Excellent service. An exceptional steak. Ambiance was also very pleasant in the building.

I was very underwhelmed with my ribeye steak.  This steak I was served was filled with gristle and inedible parts.  It was tough and lacked flavor and cost $60.  I had a $12 steak from Walmart the next night and it tasted much better.
Certainly worth a return visit. Prices are reasonable. I see why this place has a lot of positive reviews.
Great place! Love their brunch menu and the drinks here!
Incredible atmosphere with very informative staff. Meal was extremely good and future visits from me will happen.
It was pretty good, everything was tasty. Service was great

if i could give you 10 star i will defently do it. One of the best resturant i eat in, and belive me I'm traveling alot. I love the design of the place, we sit next to the kitchen so I kept looking at the kitchen staff working . Have to say they did an amazing job, you can tell by the taste and that they all the time wear gloves or wash hands. Also To see the manager/owner all the time looking around to see that everything is OK is not something you see in all resturant . Defently high class. The service is more than beyond wow. If you going to Tampa you have to stop there. Thank you for the amazing experience. And the tasty food 😋
Awesome place to eat
Perfect place
Don’t get their avocado toast, just horrible.
Excellent food and service was amazing!
A fantastic filet mignon, and probably the best reply I've ever had!
very tasty. fast, efficient, and courteous service. they have so many good reviews for a reason.
The service here is above par. The bill was well within reason for the quality.
Friendly service, good food.
Very very nice..awesome steak dinner..a little to loud with the music but other than that perfect
Not cheap but the drinks and food were great
Steelbach didn't disappoint! Steak and Mac and cheese was on point!

The waitstaff and manager were amazing. Everyone has so much personality and the atmosphere is awesome. The food was delicious in every way. For appetizers I  highly recommend the Buffalo cauliflower and the goat cheese tartine. My husband had the duck and he loved it. I had the Mac n cheese and Brussel sprouts and they were also Devine. The only thing I can say to improve is that when you box someone's food for them please include everything that was on the plate. The duck came with ribs or bones as garnish? I guess they had fat on them my husband wanted but they were not included in the take home box. Some cultures enjoy that fatty bones.
The service was amazing. My steak was cooked perfectly medium. Not an inexpensive meal, but well worth it.

Went to Steelbach for brunch today and it was absolutely wonderful. I made reservations for 11am but it really wasn't needed as it wasn't too busy for a weekend. We started with a mimosa flight and monkey bread. Everything tasted amazing-- definitely be ready to share meals here because the portions are generous and delicious. Afterwards I had the nutella French toast and a side of potatoes (could have been shared by 2 to 3 people-- again, so good!). Our visit from start to finish was great-- the service was impeccable and every dish was innovative, yet familiar.
Greatest restaurant in town

I had an excellent experience at Steelbach . My server Kyle was so gracious and attentive. I had a special request for my girlfriend and he made it happen. I will definitely be coming back. Thank you Kyle
Great dinner and drinks
Amezing food, very nice and professional staff....
Excellent food. One of my favorite places
Southern Kitchen at best!
Tomahawk was superb

What a unique restaurant!! Loved the setting and the atmosphere! The food was delicious and their dessert was excellent. As for the service, it was exceptional! Overall had a wonderful dinner date with hubby. Will definitely be back!

What a great brunch.  The pancakes have a weekly changing accompaniment of butters and syrups designed by the chef.  It was like eating dessert for breakfast.  My wife enjoyed the pork belly Benedict,  the chef's spin on a traditional Benedict with pork belly and a pimento cheese hollandaise sauce.  The only better than the food were the drinks. If you are visiting Tampa slide by Armature Works and have a meal at Steelbach, I do not think you will be disappointed.
Very expensive, little portions & very hot inside, they should put the A/C lower, I was very uncomfortable eating
Perfect place for Sunday brunch!
Fantatsic flavors & terrific staff of professionals.

This place was great! We enjoyed a tasty brunch with good drinks in an eclectic industrial elegant setting. The pulled pork was great, the jalapeno grits were delicious, and everything else just looked awesome!

My wife and I came here for our anniversary and I must say it was a great experience. We were a little hesitant to stay. because they are operating with a limited menu and I wasn't a fan of what they had to offer. However, their chef special was what saved the day. It was amazing and my wife enjoyed her grouper so we were very happy we decided to stay. The service was impressive. Kyle, our server was on top of EVERY table he attended to. The food runner Zach really impressed me when he dropped our food and explained everything on our plates. I've never been to a restaurant where a food runner was knowledgeable about the menu! Overall all, the food was great, service was great, and staff was great down to management! As someone in the industry as a manager, I definitely give this restaurant 5 stars. Great work guys! I cant wait until the menu opens back up.

I had my son's rehearsal dinner there. It was amazing. The food was great! The carrot cake was the best I've ever had!! We had a great time. The wait staff was fabulous!!! They were so professional, friendly and on point with everything!!!!
This place is amazing! Make sure to try the lamb, ribeye, potatoes, carrots and Mac n cheese. You can’t go wrong!!
Great steaks, will be back!
Delicious
Customer service was great. The Ribeye was no great.  Next time will try the Filet.  My wife had the scallop and it was amazing.
Always a good experience. Try the tomato basil soup...delicious!

The food here is totally amazing.  We had a group of 6 and all of us loved it!  The steaks were all cooked to perfection and the sides couldn't have been any better.   We had filets, ribeyes and fried chicken along with herbed potatoes,  grilled veggies,  brussel sprouts,  and nab&cheese.  We even tried the deviled eggs to get us started.

Great steak with a medley of salts  to season with and the most delicious roasted veggies.  We sat at a window seat by the fireplace then took our wine outside for sunset.  Just a great dinner.  Ask for Chris Aka.... Chris.  Thank you Sterlbach  for a great Friday night.  Highly recommend !!
We had a lovely lunch.  Good food and fine wine.  Service was excellent.
Great food & great atmosphere
Excellent
Good food. A bit overpriced. Staff was friendly. Location is good at Armature Works. Atmosphere OK.
Loved the atmosphere and the food
Good food and good service. Interesting decor inside. Would eat there again.

The popovers are melt-in-your-mouth awesome! And the tartines are so cool ! Herbed goat cheese was amazing. Great wine and beer list, amazing meat grilled over an open fire are unbelievable! We will definitely go back for other yummies.

The hubby and I came here for our anniversary dinner after being frequent Armature Works fans.  We made a reservation and when we got there a few minutes early, they were ready for us.  We were seated in a little bay window seating area which was perfect given the reason we were here; very cozy and quaint.  The vibe of the place is very industrial modern, but still warm and inviting.  We started with drinks with The Steelbach and You Look Mauvelous.  The Steelbach is very refreshing; champagne bubbles tickle your nose and it's a nice fruity flavor.  You Look Mauvelous was much sweeter with berry flavors and more of an adult fruit juice which can be dangerous.  The way their menu is setup is to order an entree and then to order sides that are big enough to split with your table, almost tapas-style.  My hubby ordered the lamb which came with two different flavored salts; one regular sea salt and another of cilantro with a cream sauce that when you put them all together is the most heavenly and tender bite of deliciousness.  The scallops were also amazing.  They sit on top of a sweet potato puree and when you dip them in it, it's a perfect blend of sweet and savory.  We ordered the roasted carrots to share which were awesome.  They're sweet and crunchy, and just like I like to make them.  For dessert, I don't like chocolate, so my choices are usually limited.  I was surprised to see that they have a hummingbird cake.  If you've never had it, it's the same texture as a carrot cake, but with more fruit inside and it has nuts on top, usually.  My hubby had never had it, but I love it since I'm not a chocolate fan.  He fell in love with it.  The frosting was creamy, but not heavy.  The candied nuts on top were a perfect bite of crunchiness and the cake itself was perfection.  We ate the entire thing.  There was nothing left on the plate.  On a side note, our waitress, Missy, was awesome.  She was so knowledgeable about everything on the menu.  She helped us out with every step and gave her opinion on everything with heart.  You can tell she really believes in the products they're putting out there.  If you're in the area, you MUST try this place out.  It does get pretty packed, but it's worth it.  Make a reservation, come hungry, and leave with a full belly and a happy food coma.

WARNING! Before eating at Steelbach if you have allergies, read this! I've never posted a horrible review, but I could have died from what they did. I gave Steelbach a hot pink allergy card and discussed with the chef himself what my allergies were and whether or not they were capable of creating a simple dish for me. It took them numerous times going back and forth assuring me they could do it. They even brought the manager over to assure me they could make me a meal. I was concerned because they said they could not give me quinoa, or corn, or most vegetables because they were all pre-prepped. A restaurant should not be a fast food already prepped place. Steelbach does not make food from scratch in their kitchen. I was given a dish with my main allergy on it which was onions. They told me no onions were in there. I thought I was eating fennel. Once I ate into it, I questioned them again, they brought it to the kitchen and then said it was onions. I was sick in their bathroom, immediately had to down emergency medication, started to swell up, got red, itchy, rashy, and very sick. My eyes were swollen and face....etc... This is serious. I don't think I will ever want to go to ANY restaurant after this. How can this even happen? I gave them an allergy card. How can they even stay in business. I've even been there before. Don't go to this restaurant if you have allergies and want to live. Don't go to this restaurant expecting a real chef that's culinary trained. I think they just have cooks. Don't go to this restaurant if you think you want to eat fresh, made from scratch food. I've eaten here before and the food was great and they were able to make me food without onions in them. I don't know what happened to them. I left only leaving a large tip for the bar. I obviously was not going to pay for being poisoned. Luckily, I was am ER nurse and had ALL the drugs I needed and this time so far didn't have to go to the ER. I'm still having the reaction, so I might need to get injectable steroids if my pill steroids and pill antihistamines don't work. Even my head itches. I did loose some weight in the bathroom though. They did offer to call an ambulance. The male bartender was beside himself with what happened. He was compassionate and extremely apologetic and could not even believe this happened to me. If you want to go to Steelbach, drink at the bar only, they won't kill you there. They have skilled, compassionate bartenders.
